iv>\n<div class="thumb tright">\n<div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="/wiki/File:K%C3%B6ppen-vereinfacht.svg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8f/K%C3%B6ppen-vereinfacht.svg/220px-K%C3%B6ppen-vereinfacht.svg.png" width="220" height="110" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8f/K%C3%B6ppen-vereinfacht.svg/330px-K%C3%B6ppen-vereinfacht.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8f/K%C3%B6ppen-vereinfacht.svg/440px-K%C3%B6ppen-vereinfacht.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="3600" data-file-height="1800" /></a>\n<div class="thumbcaption">\n<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:K%C3%B6ppen-vereinfacht.svg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>\n<b>The contemporary world</b><br />\ncommons.wikimedia.org<br />\nSee also: <a href="/wiki/Template:Clickable_world_map" title="Template:Clickable world map">Clickable world map</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>The contemporary "<a href="/wiki/Great_Divergence_(inequality)" title="Great Divergence (inequality)">Great Divergence</a>" is a term given to a period starting in late 1970s when inequality grew substantially in the <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">United States</a> and to a lesser extent in other countries such as <a href="/wiki/Canada" title="Canada">Canada</a> and the <a href="/wiki/United_Kingdom" title="United Kingdom">United Kingdom</a>. The term originated with <a href="/wiki/List_of_Nobel_laureates_in_Economics" class="mw-redirect" title="List of Nobel laureates in Economics">Nobel laureate</a>, <a href="/wiki/Princeton_University" title="Princeton University">Princeton</a> economist and <i><a href="/wiki/New_York_Times" class="mw-redirect" title="New York Times">New York Times</a></i> columnist <a href="/wiki/Paul_Krugman" title="Paul Krugman">Paul Krugman</a>,<sup id="cite_ref-39" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-39">[39]</a></sup> and is a reference to the "<a href="/wiki/Great_Compression" title="Great Compression">Great Compression</a>", an earlier era in the 1930s and 40s when income became dramatically more equal in the United States and elsewhere.<sup id="cite_ref-40" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-40">[40]</a></sup></p>\n<div class="timeline-wrapper"><map name="timeline_44223c3af4e061885019891e145e4f7a" id="timeline_44223c3af4e061885019891e145e4f7a">\n<area shape="rect" href="/wiki/Age_of_Oil" coords="426,191,531,215" title="Age of Oil" alt="Age of Oil" />\n<area shape="rect" href="/wiki/Big_Data" coords="841,165,933,189" title="Big Data" alt="Big Data" />\n<area shape="rect" href="/wiki/Information_Age" coords="668,165,806,189" title="Information Age" alt="Information Age" />\n<area shape="rect" href="/wiki/Space_Age" coords="639,139,737,163" title="Space Age" alt="Space Age" />\n<area shape="rect" href="/wiki/Cold_War" coords="526,113,618,137" title="Cold War" alt="Cold War" />\n<area shape="rect" href="/wiki/Atomic_Age" coords="591,87,696,111" title="Atomic Age" alt="Atomic Age" />\n<area shape="rect" href="/wiki/Post%2Dwar_era" coords="408,61,526,85" title="Post-war era" alt="Post-war era" />\n<area shape="rect" href="/wiki/World_War_II" coords="322,61,440,85" title="World War II" alt="World War II" />\n<area shape="rect" href="/wiki/Interwar_period" coords="207,61,345,85" title="Interwar period" alt="Interwar period" />\n<area shape="rect" href="/wiki/World_War_I" coords="126,61,238,85" title="World War I" alt="World War I" />\n<area shape="rect" href="/wiki/Machine_Age" coords="175,34,287,58" title="Machine Age" alt="Machine Age" />\n<area shape="rect" href="/wiki/2010s" coords="865,8,977,32" title="2010s" alt="2010s" />\n<area shape="rect" href="/wiki/The_Noughties" coords="797,8,895,32" title="The Noughties" alt="The Noughties" />\n<area shape="rect" href="/wiki/The_Nineties" coords="725,8,817,32" title="The Nineties" alt="The Nineties" />\n<area shape="rect" href="/wiki/The_Eighties" coords="650,8,742,32" ti